Create a modern Material Design + Bootstrap 5 application footer component named mtk-footer.

ASSUMPTIONS
- Use Material Design styles and Bootstrap 5
- Use vanilla JavaScript only
- No frameworks
- No rounded corners
- Subtle Material Design motion only
- Component must be fully JSON-driven
- Component must be load-order safe
- Do not use em dashes

CORE REQUIREMENTS
- Component name: mtk-footer
- Dark mode background
- Located at the bottom of the page
- Responsive across all breakpoints
- Content wrapped in a Bootstrap container (not container-fluid)
- Uses Material Design styling principles

LAYOUT
- Footer has one row
- Row 1
  - column 1 conains a brand with logo from "img/logo-nala-association.webp" file and description below logo
  - column 2 "Contact information". phone, email and address
  - column 3 "Social media" with icons (facebook, instagram, linkedin, youtube)

BEHAVIOR
- Footer MUST STICK to the bottom when page content height is smaller than viewport
- Footer must scroll naturally when page content exceeds viewport height
- Footer links must NOT navigate directly
- Footer link clicks must wc.publish navigation events

DATA AND CONFIGURATION
- All footer content must come from JSON
- JSON file name: mtk-footer.config.js
- Data source: window.app.footer
- JSON supports:
  - brand logo
  - brand description
  - navigation groups with titles and links
  - social icons with events

FILES TO CREATE
1. mtk-footer.config.js
2. mtk-footer.html (container only or optional static structure)
3. mtk-footer.scss
4. mtk-footer.css (compiled from SCSS)
5. mtk-footer.js (production-ready vanilla JS)

JAVASCRIPT REQUIREMENTS
- Must wait for #mtk-footer to appear in the DOM before running
- Must wait for window.app.footer to exist before rendering
- Must dynamically create internal DOM structure if missing
- Must not assume script load order
- Must not throw errors if elements are missing
- Must use an IIFE to avoid polluting the global scope

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
- html, scss, mtk-footer.config.js and mtk-footer.js
- Code must be clean, readable, and production-ready
- Do not omit error handling
- Do not hardcode text in HTML
